{
  "video_id": "HSdXqmnNCp0",
  "title": "Adam Grosser: A mobile fridge for vaccines",
  "es": 0,
  "json": [
    {
      "index": 1,
      "start_time": 13683.0,
      "end_time": 16593.0,
      "text": "This is a work in process,"
    },
    {
      "index": 2,
      "start_time": 16617.0,
      "end_time": 21152.0,
      "text": "based on some comments that were made at TED two years ago"
    },
    {
      "index": 3,
      "start_time": 21176.0,
      "end_time": 24825.0,
      "text": "about the need for the storage of vaccine."
    },
    {
      "index": 4,
      "start_time": 24849.0,
      "end_time": 26469.0,
      "text": "(Video): [On this planet"
    },
    {
      "index": 5,
      "start_time": 26493.0,
      "end_time": 29800.0,
      "text": "1.6 billion people"
    },
    {
      "index": 6,
      "start_time": 29320.0,
      "end_time": 30997.0,
      "text": "don&#39;t have access to electricity"
    },
    {
      "index": 7,
      "start_time": 31210.0,
      "end_time": 35156.0,
      "text": "refrigeration"
    },
    {
      "index": 8,
      "start_time": 35180.0,
      "end_time": 37797.0,
      "text": "or stored fuels"
    },
    {
      "index": 9,
      "start_time": 38160.0,
      "end_time": 41595.0,
      "text": "this is a problem"
    },
    {
      "index": 10,
      "start_time": 41619.0,
      "end_time": 43935.0,
      "text": "it impacts:"
    },
    {
      "index": 11,
      "start_time": 44425.0,
      "end_time": 47647.0,
      "text": "the spread of disease"
    },
    {
      "index": 12,
      "start_time": 47671.0,
      "end_time": 49479.0,
      "text": "the storage of food and medicine"
    },
    {
      "index": 13,
      "start_time": 49503.0,
      "end_time": 52605.0,
      "text": "and the quality of life."
    },
    {
      "index": 14,
      "start_time": 53430.0,
      "end_time": 55695.0,
      "text": "So here&#39;s the plan ... inexpensive refrigeration"
    },
    {
      "index": 15,
      "start_time": 55719.0,
      "end_time": 58983.0,
      "text": "that doesn&#39;t use electricity, propane, gas, kerosene or consumables"
    },
    {
      "index": 16,
      "start_time": 61159.0,
      "end_time": 63650.0,
      "text": "time for some thermodynamics"
    },
    {
      "index": 17,
      "start_time": 63675.0,
      "end_time": 66396.0,
      "text": "And the story of the Intermittent Absorption Refrigerator]"
    },
    {
      "index": 18,
      "start_time": 66421.0,
      "end_time": 69470.0,
      "text": "Adam Grosser: So 29 years ago, I had this thermo teacher"
    },
    {
      "index": 19,
      "start_time": 69710.0,
      "end_time": 72173.0,
      "text": "who talked about absorption and refrigeration, one of those things"
    },
    {
      "index": 20,
      "start_time": 72198.0,
      "end_time": 74726.0,
      "text": "that stuck in my head, a lot like the Stirling engine:"
    },
    {
      "index": 21,
      "start_time": 74750.0,
      "end_time": 77201.0,
      "text": "it was cool, but you didn&#39;t know what to do with it."
    },
    {
      "index": 22,
      "start_time": 77225.0,
      "end_time": 79774.0,
      "text": "It was invented in 1858, by this guy Ferdinand Carr√©,"
    },
    {
      "index": 23,
      "start_time": 79799.0,
      "end_time": 82640.0,
      "text": "but he couldn&#39;t actually build anything with it"
    },
    {
      "index": 24,
      "start_time": 82880.0,
      "end_time": 83708.0,
      "text": "because of the tools at the time."
    },
    {
      "index": 25,
      "start_time": 83733.0,
      "end_time": 87973.0,
      "text": "This crazy Canadian named Powel Crosley commercialized this thing"
    },
    {
      "index": 26,
      "start_time": 87997.0,
      "end_time": 89997.0,
      "text": "called the IcyBall, in 1928."
    },
    {
      "index": 27,
      "start_time": 90210.0,
      "end_time": 93620.0,
      "text": "It was a really neat idea, and I&#39;ll get to why it didn&#39;t work,"
    },
    {
      "index": 28,
      "start_time": 93860.0,
      "end_time": 94260.0,
      "text": "but here&#39;s how it works."
    },
    {
      "index": 29,
      "start_time": 94284.0,
      "end_time": 96860.0,
      "text": "There&#39;s two spheres and they&#39;re separated in distance."
    },
    {
      "index": 30,
      "start_time": 96884.0,
      "end_time": 99240.0,
      "text": "One has a working fluid, water and ammonia,"
    },
    {
      "index": 31,
      "start_time": 99264.0,
      "end_time": 100851.0,
      "text": "and the other is a condenser."
    },
    {
      "index": 32,
      "start_time": 100876.0,
      "end_time": 102841.0,
      "text": "You heat up one side, the hot side."
    },
    {
      "index": 33,
      "start_time": 102865.0,
      "end_time": 105884.0,
      "text": "The ammonia evaporates and it recondenses in the other side."
    },
    {
      "index": 34,
      "start_time": 105908.0,
      "end_time": 108446.0,
      "text": "You let it cool to room temperature,"
    },
    {
      "index": 35,
      "start_time": 108470.0,
      "end_time": 111633.0,
      "text": "and then, as the ammonia reevaporates and combines with the water"
    },
    {
      "index": 36,
      "start_time": 111657.0,
      "end_time": 113259.0,
      "text": "back on the erstwhile hot side,"
    },
    {
      "index": 37,
      "start_time": 113284.0,
      "end_time": 115138.0,
      "text": "it creates a powerful cooling effect."
    },
    {
      "index": 38,
      "start_time": 115577.0,
      "end_time": 117994.0,
      "text": "So it was a great idea that didn&#39;t work at all."
    },
    {
      "index": 39,
      "start_time": 118180.0,
      "end_time": 119212.0,
      "text": "They blew up."
    },
    {
      "index": 40,
      "start_time": 119236.0,
      "end_time": 120771.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 41,
      "start_time": 120795.0,
      "end_time": 123582.0,
      "text": "Because you&#39;re using ammonia, you get hugely high pressures"
    },
    {
      "index": 42,
      "start_time": 123606.0,
      "end_time": 124872.0,
      "text": "if you heated them wrong;"
    },
    {
      "index": 43,
      "start_time": 124897.0,
      "end_time": 126652.0,
      "text": "it topped 400 psi."
    },
    {
      "index": 44,
      "start_time": 126676.0,
      "end_time": 128816.0,
      "text": "The ammonia was toxic, it sprayed everywhere."
    },
    {
      "index": 45,
      "start_time": 128840.0,
      "end_time": 131120.0,
      "text": "But it was kind of an interesting thought."
    },
    {
      "index": 46,
      "start_time": 131360.0,
      "end_time": 133468.0,
      "text": "So the great thing about 2006,"
    },
    {
      "index": 47,
      "start_time": 133492.0,
      "end_time": 136346.0,
      "text": "there&#39;s a lot of really great computational work you can do."
    },
    {
      "index": 48,
      "start_time": 136371.0,
      "end_time": 140446.0,
      "text": "So we got the whole thermodynamics department at Stanford involved --"
    },
    {
      "index": 49,
      "start_time": 140470.0,
      "end_time": 142300.0,
      "text": "a lot of computational fluid dynamics."
    },
    {
      "index": 50,
      "start_time": 142324.0,
      "end_time": 146259.0,
      "text": "We proved that most of the ammonia refrigeration tables are wrong."
    },
    {
      "index": 51,
      "start_time": 146283.0,
      "end_time": 148335.0,
      "text": "We found some nontoxic refrigerants"
    },
    {
      "index": 52,
      "start_time": 148360.0,
      "end_time": 150471.0,
      "text": "that worked at very low vapor pressures."
    },
    {
      "index": 53,
      "start_time": 150962.0,
      "end_time": 152650.0,
      "text": "We brought in a team from the UK --"
    },
    {
      "index": 54,
      "start_time": 152675.0,
      "end_time": 155650.0,
      "text": "a lot of great refrigeration people, it turns out, in the UK --"
    },
    {
      "index": 55,
      "start_time": 155674.0,
      "end_time": 157954.0,
      "text": "and built a test rig, and proved that, in fact,"
    },
    {
      "index": 56,
      "start_time": 157978.0,
      "end_time": 161221.0,
      "text": "we could make a low-pressure, nontoxic refrigerator."
    },
    {
      "index": 57,
      "start_time": 161245.0,
      "end_time": 162593.0,
      "text": "So this is the way it works."
    },
    {
      "index": 58,
      "start_time": 162617.0,
      "end_time": 164290.0,
      "text": "You put it on a cooking fire."
    },
    {
      "index": 59,
      "start_time": 164530.0,
      "end_time": 166163.0,
      "text": "Most people have cooking fires in the world,"
    },
    {
      "index": 60,
      "start_time": 166187.0,
      "end_time": 167741.0,
      "text": "whether it&#39;s camel dung or wood."
    },
    {
      "index": 61,
      "start_time": 167765.0,
      "end_time": 170452.0,
      "text": "It heats up for about 30 minutes, cools for an hour."
    },
    {
      "index": 62,
      "start_time": 171570.0,
      "end_time": 175249.0,
      "text": "You put it into a container and it will refrigerate for 24 hours."
    },
    {
      "index": 63,
      "start_time": 175273.0,
      "end_time": 176495.0,
      "text": "It looks like this."
    },
    {
      "index": 64,
      "start_time": 176519.0,
      "end_time": 179336.0,
      "text": "This is the fifth prototype, it&#39;s not quite done."
    },
    {
      "index": 65,
      "start_time": 179360.0,
      "end_time": 182344.0,
      "text": "It weighs about eight pounds, and this is the way it works."
    },
    {
      "index": 66,
      "start_time": 182368.0,
      "end_time": 185950.0,
      "text": "You put it into a 15-liter vessel, about three gallons,"
    },
    {
      "index": 67,
      "start_time": 185974.0,
      "end_time": 188446.0,
      "text": "and it&#39;ll cool it down to just above freezing --"
    },
    {
      "index": 68,
      "start_time": 188470.0,
      "end_time": 189948.0,
      "text": "three degrees above freezing --"
    },
    {
      "index": 69,
      "start_time": 189972.0,
      "end_time": 193120.0,
      "text": "for 24 hours in a 30 degree C environment."
    },
    {
      "index": 70,
      "start_time": 193360.0,
      "end_time": 194223.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s really cheap."
    },
    {
      "index": 71,
      "start_time": 194247.0,
      "end_time": 197323.0,
      "text": "We think we can build these in high volumes for about 25 dollars,"
    },
    {
      "index": 72,
      "start_time": 197347.0,
      "end_time": 199780.0,
      "text": "in low volumes for about 40 dollars."
    },
    {
      "index": 73,
      "start_time": 199102.0,
      "end_time": 202572.0,
      "text": "And we think we can make refrigeration something that everybody can have."
    },
    {
      "index": 74,
      "start_time": 202596.0,
      "end_time": 203772.0,
      "text": "Thank you."
    },
    {
      "index": 75,
      "start_time": 203796.0,
      "end_time": 206170.0,
      "text": "(Applause)"
    }
  ]
}